The paper focuses on software development and proposes a context-aware code recommendation approach for exception handling. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing and filtering code examples, which could fall under Programming Languages (cs.PL). The use of heuristic quality measures and the ranking of examples suggest that Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) could also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves leveraging features of exception handlers, which could fall under the Software Systems (cs.SI) sub-category.
